{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Manage-VMClasses\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 VM Class Management\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Tools for discovering VM configurations from a vCenter and managing vCenter Supervisor VM class definitions.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Prerequisites\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab PowerShell 7.4 or later {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/scripting/install/install-powershell"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
download
}}}
.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab VCF PowerCLI 9.0+ {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.broadcom.com/powercli/installation-guide"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
download
}}}
.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Network access to vCenter.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A user with the following rights, at minimum, to the source vCenter: Read-only (at vCenter root level).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A user with the following rights, at minimum, to the destination vCenter: Namespaces.Configure and Namespaces.ListAccess.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Script: {\f1 Manage-VMClasses.ps1}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A single script that covers the full lifecycle of Supervisor VM classes \u8212- discover, list, backup, update, and delete.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Authentication\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The script always prompts for credentials interactively unless you set the {\f1 VCENTER_PASSWORD} environment variable before running it. Use this for CI/CD or non-interactive pipelines. This option is not compatible with interactive mode.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi0 {\b Note:} if the password is incorrect, you will be prompted to enter your username and password interactively.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Example\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 > $env:VCENTER_PASSWORD = "<elided>"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Interactive (default)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 .\\Manage-VMClasses.ps1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 Non-interactive\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 .\\Manage-VMClasses.ps1 -VcenterServer vcenter.example.com -VcenterUser admininstrator@vsphere.local -Action [Discover|List|Backup|Update|Delete]\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Actions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 {\f1 Discover} \u8212- Scan live VMs and generate a class definition file\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Connects to vCenter, enumerates all VMs, and groups them by unique CPU / memory / GPU configuration. An interactive table lets you select which groups to include (including all). The selected configurations are written to the file {\f1 vmClasses.json} by default, or to the path you specify with {\f1 -JsonPath}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If the output file already exists, the script prompts you to overwrite it, enter a different path, or cancel. Pass {\f1 -Force} parameter to overwrite without prompting, and {\f1 -SaveAll} to skip the selection table and save every discovered configuration automatically. Combine both for a fully non-interactive run.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 # Interactive discovery; writes vmClasses.json\line
.\\Manage-VMClasses.ps1 -Action Discover -VcenterServer vcenter.example.com -VcenterUser admininstrator@vsphere.local\line
\line
# Write to a custom path\line
.\\Manage-VMClasses.ps1 -Action Discover -VcenterServer vcenter.example.com -VcenterUser admininstrator@vsphere.local `\line
    -JsonPath .\\my-classes.json\line
\line
# Overwrite an existing file without prompting\line
.\\Manage-VMClasses.ps1 -Action Discover -VcenterServer vcenter.example.com -VcenterUser admininstrator@vsphere.local `\line
    -Force\line
\line
# Fully non-interactive: save all configurations, overwrite existing file\line
.\\Manage-VMClasses.ps1 -Action Discover -VcenterServer vcenter.example.com -VcenterUser admininstrator@vsphere.local `\line
    -SaveAll -Force\line
\line
# Example:\line
\line
.\\Manage-VMClasses.ps1 -Action Discover -VcenterServer vcenter.example.com -VcenterUser administrator@vsphere.local -Force -SaveAll\line
\line
