{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel3 \b \fs24 {\f1 List} \u8212- Print all VM classes on vCenter\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Prints a table of all VM classes (Name, CpuCount, MemoryMB, Default, Gpu). The {\b Default} column shows {\b Yes} for the 16 pre-defined vCenter class names and {\b No} for any custom classes. No JSON file is required.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 # List all VM classes\line
.\\Manage-VMClasses.ps1 -Action List -VcenterServer vcenter.example.com -VcenterUser admininstrator@vsphere.local\line
\line
# Example\line
 .\\Manage-VMClasses.ps1 -Action List -VcenterServer vdest-vcenter.example.com -VcenterUser administrator@vsphere.local\line
\line
