{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Interactive guided workflow (no {\f1 -Action})\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Running the script without {\f1 -Action} displays an arrow-key menu in the order {\b Discover \u8594 ? List \u8594 ? Backup \u8594 ? Update \u8594 ? Delete \u8594 ? Help \u8594 ? Quit}. Selecting an action chains automatically into the next logical steps:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Discover} \u8212- connects to a source vCenter, scans VMs, writes the JSON. Offers to exit for manual class-name editing, or continues to an import flow (pre-backup \u8594 ? Update \u8594 ? post-backup) against the same or a different destination vCenter.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b List} \u8212- connects to destination vCenter, lists classes, then optionally takes a pre-import backup, runs an import, and takes a post-import backup.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Backup} \u8212- connects to destination vCenter, takes a timestamped backup.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Update} \u8212- connects to source vCenter, imports classes, then optionally removes a class and lists the final state.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Delete} \u8212- connects to destination vCenter, takes a pre-delete backup, removes selected classes, lists remaining classes, takes a post-delete backup.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 All workflow backup files are saved in a {\f1 Backup/} subdirectory next to the script, with filenames that embed the vCenter name, qualifier ({\f1 pre}/{\f1 post}), and timestamp for easy identification.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
